   <activity xml:id="infinity-rational1">
        <introduction>
            <p>
   Recall that a rational function is a ratio of two polynomials. For any given rational function, what are all the possible behaviors as <m>x</m> tends to + or - infinity?
            </p>
        </introduction>

            <ol marker="A.">
                <li><p>The only possible limit is <m>0</m></p></li>
                <li><p>The only possible limits are <m>0</m> or <m>\pm \infty</m>
 </p></li>
                <li><p>The only possible limits are <m>0</m>, <m>1</m> or <m>\pm \infty</m>
 </p></li>
                        <li><p>The only possible limits are any constant number or <m>\pm \infty</m></p></li>
            </ol>

    </activity>


